description: This is the main entry point for a React web application. It sets up ReactDOM rendering for the root component, 'App', within a DOM element with ID 'root', and wraps it with React.StrictMode for highlighting potential issues.

methods.name: ReactDOM.createRoot
methods.description: Creates a React root for rendering the React component tree into the specified DOM element.

methods.name: root.render
methods.description: Renders the React component subtree into the root DOM node.
